.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:33:<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_md -->
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:35:Routes non-trivial user requests to the right skill through the standalone Skill Advisor MCP package.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:41:Use this skill when the work is about skill selection, Gate 2 routing, advisor MCP tools, prompt-time skill-advisor hooks, skill graph freshness or the standalone advisor package.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:45:- A request asks which skill should handle a task.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:46:- A runtime hook needs a skill recommendation before execution.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:47:- An operator asks about `advisor_recommend`, `advisor_status`, `advisor_rebuild`, `advisor_validate`, `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_query`, `skill_graph_status`, `skill_graph_validate` or `skill_graph_propagate_enhances`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:48:- A packet touches the skill graph, skill metadata, advisor scorer, advisor feature catalog or manual testing playbook.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:51:Do not use this skill as a replacement for the recommended target skill. For example, route code implementation to `sk-code`, documentation authoring to `sk-doc`, git work to `sk-git` and MCP orchestration to `mcp-code-mode` after the advisor has made the recommendation.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:57:This package is mandatory context for non-trivial Gate 2 routing. The live advisor scores prompts through `mk_skill_advisor`; this smart router controls which local documentation resources an agent should load while maintaining the advisor package.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:64:  +-- exact skill name or explicit user direction -> named skill wins
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:66:  +-- non-trivial or ambiguous request
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:68:        +-- advisor_recommend on mk_skill_advisor MCP
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:70:        +-- top recommendation above confidence threshold -> invoke that skill
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:72:        +-- ambiguous top scores -> surface top candidates and ask or route with caveat
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:77:- `references/scoring/` documents scorer lanes, lane weight tuning, calibration and validation baselines.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:78:- `references/graph/` documents skill graph queries, drift reconciliation, graph extraction status and `enhances` propagation.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:79:- `references/runtime/` documents standalone MCP topology, stable tool ids, bridge policy, freshness and daemon lease behavior.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:80:- `references/config/` documents package-local database path policy.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/SKILL.md:81:- `references/hooks/` documents prompt-time hook behavior across runtimes.
