.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:3:description: Template for per-feature scenario files stored directly under manual_testing_playbook category directories.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:8:Per-feature scenario files for split manual testing playbooks. Use this template for the one-file-per-feature contract described in the main playbook template.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:10:> **EXECUTION POLICY**: Every scenario MUST be executed for real — not mocked, not stubbed, not classified as "unautomatable". AI agents executing these scenarios must run the actual commands, inspect real files, call real handlers, and verify real outputs. The only acceptable classifications are PASS, FAIL, or SKIP (with a specific sandbox blocker documented). "UNAUTOMATABLE" is not a valid status.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:16:Each feature file is the canonical home for full scenario execution detail. The root `manual_testing_playbook.md` stays readable by summarizing the feature and linking here, while the feature file carries the realistic user-testing context, orchestration process, 9-column test row, structured source references, and concise metadata. The file shape should intentionally mirror the Feature Catalog snippet pattern so operators can move between the catalog and the playbook without relearning the document structure.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:21:- Frontmatter that mirrors the larger root docs (`title` + `description`)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:22:- Root playbook summary plus per-feature file cross-link
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_snippet_template.md:31:**Validator note**: The current validator checks markdown structure on the root playbook. It does not recurse into category folders or verify cross-file links.
