.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:3:description: "Ambiguity detection that returns an ambiguous brief when the top two candidates are within 0.05 on EITHER score or confidence."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:5:  - "ambiguity window"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:6:  - "top 2 ambiguity"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:7:  - "ambiguous brief"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:8:  - "0.05 ambiguity window"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:9:  - "dual-margin ambiguity"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:14:<!-- sk-doc-template: skill_asset_feature_catalog -->
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:18:Avoid silently picking a single winner when two candidates are tied or near-tied. Expose the ambiguity to callers so routing decisions stay honest under the 5-lane fusion.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:22:`lib/scorer/ambiguity.ts` evaluates a **dual-margin OR** predicate against the top-1 candidate. A candidate joins the ambiguity cluster when the gap on EITHER axis is within 0.05:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:24:- `AMBIGUITY_MARGIN = 0.05` on aggregate `score` (keeps cluster aligned with the score-based fusion ranking, F-012-C2-04 invariant).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:25:- `AMBIGUITY_CONFIDENCE_MARGIN = 0.05` on `confidence` (catches user-visible near-ties when score gap just exceeds margin, Packet 084, SAD-002 fix).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:27:If either gap is within margin, the response carries an ambiguity signal that the render path surfaces as an ambiguous brief. A candidate is unambiguously ranked only when **both** gaps exceed margin.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/feature_catalog/04--scorer-fusion/03-ambiguity.md:35:| `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/lib/scorer/ambiguity.ts` | Library | Source reference |
