.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:3:description: Template for human-facing skill README files that explain purpose, routing, resources, usage, validation and related documents.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:8:Use this template for `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/README.md`. It narrows the generic README structure to OpenCode skill packages.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:16:Provide a human-facing README scaffold for OpenCode skill packages without duplicating runtime instructions from `SKILL.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:20:Copy the fillable scaffold into `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/README.md`, replace placeholders with current skill behavior, then remove sections that do not fit.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:26:| Target path | `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/README.md` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:35:- The skill has multiple operating modes, references, assets or scripts.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:36:- Operators need quick-start commands or validation steps.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:37:- The skill participates in skill graph navigation or runtime routing.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:38:- The skill has troubleshooting, FAQ or usage examples worth preserving outside `SKILL.md`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:40:Keep the content in `SKILL.md` when the skill is tiny and runtime instructions already give complete human orientation.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:46:Existing skill READMEs in this workspace commonly use this structure:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:50:| Frontmatter | Search and routing metadata | Usually, for discoverable skills |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:54:| How This Compares | Boundary with nearby skills | Readers may confuse responsibilities |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:64:Do not copy spec packet history into a skill README. Document current behavior with stable paths and commands.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md:66:This structure is derived from `assets/readme/readme_template.md` and aligned with the asset-file overview pattern in `skill_asset_template.md`.
