.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:6:  - "advisor lease semantics"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:21:Defines workspace single-writer lease semantics for the advisor freshness daemon.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:27:- Checking why two advisor processes must not write concurrently.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:31:Only one advisor daemon may hold the workspace lease for a resolved database directory at a time.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:45:The `mk-skill-advisor-launcher.cjs` script enforces single-writer semantics at process startup before opening the SQLite skill-graph database. It calls `isLeaseHeld()` from `lib/daemon/lease.ts` to probe the lease state:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:55:Daemon attempts lease acquisition on startup. The lease database lives next to the canonical skill graph database directory as `skill-graph-daemon-lease.sqlite`. Canonical means lexical `path.resolve()` followed by `fs.realpathSync.native()` when the path exists; if the directory did not exist yet, the daemon creates it and canonicalizes again before deriving the `workspace_key`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:57:With the default configuration that directory is `.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/`. With `MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR` or `SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR`, the override relocates both `skill-graph.sqlite` and `skill-graph-daemon-lease.sqlite` together. On success the lease row records:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:76:Every skill-graph database open sets `PRAGMA journal_mode=WAL` and `PRAGMA busy_timeout=5000` to improve concurrency safety and handle short-term lock contention. If the filesystem is read-only (EACCES), WAL mode falls back to `journal_mode=DELETE` with a logged warning.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:84:If the lease holder responds with an MCP `advisor_status` call showing `live` trust state, the waiter accepts the holder as canonical plus exits without competing. If the holder is unresponsive past 3 retry cycles, the waiter inspects the heartbeat timestamp. If stale (>2x heartbeat interval), the waiter triggers stale-lease recovery (see §4).
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:108:During the Phase 006 compatibility window, launcher startup also probes the old lease database at `.opencode/skills/.advisor-state/skill-graph-daemon-lease.sqlite`. If that legacy database contains a live owner, the launcher exits `0` with `LEASE_HELD_BY:<pid> ... (legacy path)` and does not open the skill graph DB. If the legacy owner is stale or dead, startup logs the stale legacy observation and proceeds with the canonical lease beside the resolved DB directory. The launcher observes but does not migrate the legacy database.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:116:| Lease holder PID killed without releasing | New daemon waits until the row is stale | Stale-lease recovery fires after heartbeat timeout. If recovery itself fails, inspect `skill-graph-daemon-lease.sqlite` beside the DB directory |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:119:| Two daemons acquire concurrently due to filesystem race | SQLite database shows corruption (rare on macOS APFS, possible on NFS) | Stop both daemons. Delete `skill-graph.sqlite{,-wal,-shm}`. Run `advisor_rebuild --force` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:121:| Lease database corruption | Daemon refuses to read the lease | Delete `skill-graph-daemon-lease.sqlite`. Re-acquire. The lease format is non-critical state |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:127:`MK_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR` and `SYSTEM_SKILL_ADVISOR_DB_DIR` override the skill graph database directory. The daemon lease database is co-located with that canonical directory, so two workspaces pointing at the same SQLite directory through different symlinks or path aliases share the same single-writer boundary.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:148:- [`validation_baselines.md`](../scoring/validation_baselines.md), latency baselines that depend on lease cleanliness
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/daemon_lease_contract.md:150:- `manual_testing_playbook/05--auto-update-daemon/002-lease-single-writer.md`, operator scenario
