.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:3:description: "Baseline metrics for advisor_validate (corpus, holdout, UNKNOWN, daemon, cache latency) plus the troubleshooting playbook when a slice regresses."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:5:  - "advisor validation baselines"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:7:  - "advisor_validate troubleshooting"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:13:Baseline metrics for advisor_validate (corpus, holdout, UNKNOWN, daemon, cache latency) plus the troubleshooting playbook when a slice regresses.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:21:Captures `advisor_validate` baseline metrics and the troubleshooting playbook for validation slice regressions.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:25:- Running release validation after scorer, metadata or graph changes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:31:Validation baselines are the promotion gate for routing behavior changes, not after-the-fact reporting.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:36:- [`advisor_scorer.md`](./advisor_scorer.md)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:43:Baseline numbers as of remediation SHA `97a318d83`:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:47:| Full-corpus top-1 accuracy | 80.5% | `mcp_server/tests/scorer/corpus.vitest.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:48:| Holdout top-1 accuracy | 77.5% | `mcp_server/tests/scorer/holdout.vitest.ts` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:49:| UNKNOWN count (full corpus) | <= 10 | `advisor_validate` `telemetry.unknownCount` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:50:| Python regression suite | full pass | `mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_regression.py` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:52:| Watcher idle CPU | 0.031% | `mcp_server/lib/daemon/watcher.ts` benchmark |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:63:`advisor_validate` is a heavy operation. It runs the full corpus plus holdout plus parity plus safety plus latency slices in one pass. Require `confirmHeavyRun=true` to invoke.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:66:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate({ "confirmHeavyRun": true })
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:69:For a single-skill check (skip corpus + holdout):
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:72:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate({ "confirmHeavyRun": true, "skillSlug": "sk-code" })
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:85:- `perSkill[]` (array of per-skill results)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:94:Runs every skill in the full corpus through the scorer. Top-1 accuracy is the percent of prompts where the correct skill ranks first. Baseline 80.5%.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:96:Drift signal: a drop of more than 2 percentage points. Likely causes are scorer weight changes, new skills disrupting the lexical lane or stale skill metadata.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:100:Runs a curated subset reserved for measuring generalization. Top-1 accuracy is the percent where the correct skill ranks first. Baseline 77.5%.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:106:Checks that the Python shim plus the native MCP scorer return the same recommendations for the same prompt. Pass means parity holds.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:128:| Corpus top-1 drops > 2pp | Scorer weight change OR new skill metadata regression | Run `advisor_rebuild --force`. If still regressed, inspect `perSkill[]` for the regressed skills. Roll back weights per `lane_weight_tuning.md` §6 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:129:| Holdout top-1 drops while corpus stays steady | Overfit to corpus | Inspect which holdout prompts misroute. Add representative cases to corpus. Re-run tuning |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:130:| UNKNOWN count spikes above 10 | Trust-state went to `absent` OR scorer threshold misconfigured | Check `advisor_status.trustState`. If `absent`, run `advisor_rebuild`. If `live`, inspect lane weights for an over-aggressive threshold |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:131:| Parity slice fails on specific skill | Python shim missing recent token boost added to native scorer | Re-sync `scripts/skill_advisor.py` against `mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:133:| Cache-hit p95 > 15 ms | SQLite contention | Check `advisor_status.daemon.leaseHolder`. If contested, kill stale processes. Verify `mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite` integrity |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:135:| `advisor_validate` errors with `confirmHeavyRun is required` | Caller did not opt in | Pass `confirmHeavyRun: true` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:136:| `advisor_validate` hangs > 5 min | Daemon lock OR test-corpus growth | Check process via `ps`. If hung, kill the MCP server plus restart. If completion exceeds 5 min routinely, trim test corpus or split into incremental runs |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:142:- [`tool_ids_reference.md`](../runtime/tool_ids_reference.md) §2, `advisor_validate` input plus output schema
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:144:- [`advisor_scorer.md`](./advisor_scorer.md), scorer mechanics that the validate slices probe
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:147:- `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-validate.ts`, handler implementation
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/scoring/validation_baselines.md:148:- `mcp_server/bench/`, latency benchmark harnesses
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:3:description: "Manual validation that includeAttribution: true returns per-lane contribution metadata (lane, rawScore, weight, weightedScore, shadowOnly) without leaking prompt content."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:13:<!-- sk-doc-template: manual_testing_playbook -->
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:19:Validate that `includeAttribution: true` returns per-lane `lane`, `rawScore`, `weight`, `weightedScore` and `shadowOnly` metadata via `lib/scorer/attribution.ts` and that no prompt text or prompt-derived evidence snippets appear in the attribution output.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:26:- Any prompt that routes to a known skill.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:32:> **Structure deviation note (007-deferred-final).** This scenario uses a numbered-step plus Expected Signals plus Failure Modes shape instead of the canonical Prompt/Commands/Expected/Evidence/Pass-Fail/Failure-Triage subsections. The deviation is intentional for this skill playbook category to keep scenario semantics tightly bound to runtime output checks. See `references/decisions/deferred_decisions.md` §F34 for rationale.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:37:advisor_recommend({"prompt":"review this pull request","options":{"topK":1,"includeAttribution":true}})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:46:- With `includeAttribution: true`, each lane entry carries exactly the documented fields: `lane`, `rawScore`, `weight`, `weightedScore`, `shadowOnly`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/manual_testing_playbook/08--scorer-fusion/004-lane-attribution.md:47:- `semantic_shadow` reports `shadowOnly: false` (it is a live lane at registry weight 0.05; fusion derives the flag from lane liveness).
