.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:21:Lists the stable public and internal `system-skill-advisor` MCP tool IDs with namespaces, purposes and schema signals.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:25:- Confirming the exact advisor or skill graph tool id to call.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:26:- Updating routing docs, hooks or compatibility shims.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:36:- `mcp_server/tools/skill-graph-tools.ts`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:45:| `advisor_recommend` | Recommend skills for a prompt using the native scorer. Returns prompt-safe recommendations, lane attribution, lifecycle redirects, cache state, freshness and trust. | `prompt`, optional `options.topK`, `options.includeAttribution` | `recommendations[]`, `freshness`, `trustState`, `cache`, `_shadow` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:46:| `advisor_rebuild` | Rebuild the native advisor skill graph from checked-in metadata. Use when `advisor_status` reports stale or absent. | `force`, optional `workspaceRoot` | `rebuilt`, `skipped`, `reason`, generation deltas, `skillCount`, `diagnostics` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:47:| `advisor_status` | Report advisor freshness, skill-graph generation, trust state, lane weights and daemon availability without exposing prompt content. | `workspaceRoot`, optional `maxMetadataFiles` | `freshness`, `generation`, `trustState`, lane weights, daemon info, `errors` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:48:| `advisor_validate` | Run the native advisor regression bundle. Requires `confirmHeavyRun=true` because it executes heavier validation work. | `confirmHeavyRun`, optional `skillSlug`, optional `outcomeEvents[]` | `overallAccuracy`, `perSkill[]`, slices for corpus, holdout, parity, safety, latency, `telemetry`, `generatedAt` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:56:| `skill_graph_scan` | Index or re-index all `.opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json` files into `skill-graph.sqlite` using the hash-aware SQLite indexer. | optional `skillsRoot` (default `.opencode/skills`) | `scanResult`, `embeddings`, `sourceSignature` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:57:| `skill_graph_query` | Query the SQLite-backed skill graph using structural relationship traversals. Supports `depends_on`, `dependents`, `enhances`, `enhanced_by`, `family_members`, `conflicts`, `transitive_path`, `hub_skills`, `orphans` and `subgraph`. | `queryType` plus query-specific arguments | varies by `queryType` (`relationships[]`, `members[]`, `path[]`, `skills[]`, `graph{}`) |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:58:| `skill_graph_status` | Report skill graph health from the live SQLite database. | (none) | `totalSkills`, `totalEdges`, `lastIndexedAt`, `families`, `categories`, `schemaVersions`, `staleness`, `validation`, `dbStatus` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:59:| `skill_graph_validate` | Validate the live skill graph for schema-version drift, broken edges, weight-band violations, reciprocal symmetry and dependency cycles. | (none) | `isValid`, `errorCount`, `warningCount`, `checkedNodes`, `checkedEdges`, `errors[]`, `warnings[]` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:60:| `skill_graph_propagate_enhances` | Detect, report and optionally apply missing inbound `edges.enhances[]` declarations across skills. Default mode is `report` (no writes). | optional `skillsRoot`, `mode`, `minConfidence`, `applyCandidateIds[]`, `applyAllHighConfidence`, `dryRun` | `candidates{detected[], proposed[], applied[]}`, `confidenceScores{}`, `dryRun`, `warnings[]` |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:68:| `skill_graph_propagate_enhances` | Internal authoring helper for missing `enhances` edges. See [propagate_enhances.md](../graph/propagate_enhances.md). | `requireTrustedCaller` plus workspace-escape guard |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:70:The tool ships in the skill-graph tool set and appears in Section 3 for completeness. Section 4 documents its access gates. Untrusted callers are rejected before detection runs.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:76:All tools follow the pattern `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__<tool_name>` where `<tool_name>` matches the descriptor's `name` field in snake_case.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:80:- `advisor_recommend` is reachable as `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_recommend`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:81:- `skill_graph_query` is reachable as `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_query`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/tool_ids_reference.md:82:- `skill_graph_propagate_enhances` is reachable as `mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_propagate_enhances`.
