.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:3:description: Templates and guidelines for creating effective SKILL.md files for AI agent skills with complete scaffolds and section guidance.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:16:SKILL.md files define AI agent skills - reusable capabilities that extend an agent's functionality for specific domains or workflows. A well-crafted SKILL.md:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:25:This guide provides **one comprehensive SKILL template** (Section 3) that covers all skill types from simple single-purpose tools to complex multi-mode orchestrators.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:28:- **Simple skills**: Use required core sections only (WHEN TO USE, SMART ROUTING, HOW IT WORKS, RULES, REFERENCES)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:29:- **Skills with bundled resources**: Include detection context, merged resource domains/mapping, loading levels, and one authoritative Smart Router Pseudocode block; use `references/`, `assets/`, and `scripts/`
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:30:- **Multi-mode skills**: Expand WHEN TO USE and HOW IT WORKS sections by mode
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:31:- **All skills**: MUST include Section 2 (SMART ROUTING) with detection guidance + domain-based routing + pseudocode
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:36:- Simple: Unit test generator, documentation formatter (no bundled resources)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:38:- Complex: Workflow orchestrator, document quality pipeline (multi-mode with extensive resources)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:45:2. **SKILL.md body** - When skill activates (<5k words)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:74:| `name` | ✅ | hyphen-case | `my-skill-name` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:75:| `description` | ✅ | Single line, **≤ 130 chars** for skills (≤ 110 for commands); 1,536-char hard cap | `"Handles X when Y occurs"` |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:79:> **Description budget & trim style**: see [`frontmatter_templates.md` § Description Budget & Trim Style](../frontmatter_templates.md). Total project descriptions must stay under ~5,600 chars or Claude Code will silently drop the longest from auto-discovery. Authoring rules: drop product/stack enumerations, drop marketing prose; keep skill name, primary verb, domain noun, and mode suffixes (`:auto`/`:confirm`).
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:86:description: Example workflow skill demonstrating proper frontmatter format with specific capabilities, use cases, and key differentiators for AI agent discovery.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:98:> **Complete Reference**: For validation rules, edge cases, array formats, and all document type frontmatter, see [frontmatter_templates.md](frontmatter_templates.md)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:108:**Size Constraints** (package_skill.py validation):
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:115:- `package_skill.py` fails if `REFERENCES` is missing and no approved combined `SMART ROUTING & REFERENCES` structure exists.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:122:name: example-skill
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:123:description: Example skill demonstrating proper template structure with specific capabilities for semantic code search and context preservation workflows.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:134:<!-- OPTIONAL: Include this block if skill has a supplemental navigation layer.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:135:     See skill_creation.md for authoring rules. -->
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:151:- [Pattern 1 that triggers skill]
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:152:- [Pattern 2 that triggers skill]
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:175:<!-- CRITICAL: Keep one authoritative Smart Router Pseudocode block in this section.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:176:     Detection context may appear before pseudocode. Do NOT duplicate routing logic in separate lookup tables. -->
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:183:# Example (replace with skill-specific detection)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:194:    +- STEP 1: Score intents (top-2 when ambiguity is small)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:202:The router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/` and then applies intent scoring from `INTENT_MODEL`.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:219:| ALWAYS      | Every skill invocation   | Baseline references          |
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:223:### Smart Router Pseudocode
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:227:> Pattern: see [sk-doc smart-router resilience template](./skill_smart_router.md) for the full runtime discovery, guarded load, routing-key, and fallback reference.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:229:New skills fill in the domain-specific `INTENT_MODEL`, `RESOURCE_MAP`, loading levels, and routing key detector while keeping the resilience mechanics unchanged: discover resources at runtime, guard every path before loading, derive a routing key from the task or runtime, and return an `UNKNOWN_FALLBACK` checklist when confidence is too low.
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:265:def _guard_in_skill(relative_path: str) -> str:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:273:    docs = []
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:276:            docs.extend(path for path in base.rglob("*.md") if path.is_file())
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:277:    return {doc.relative_to(SKILL_ROOT).as_posix() for doc in docs}
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:287:    scores = {intent: 0 for intent in INTENT_MODEL}
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:291:                scores[intent] += weight
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:293:    ranked = sorted(scores.items(), key=lambda pair: pair[1], reverse=True)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:294:    primary, primary_score = ranked[0]
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:295:    if primary_score == 0:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:296:        return ("PRIMARY", None, scores)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:298:    secondary, secondary_score = ranked[1]
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:299:    if secondary_score > 0 and (primary_score - secondary_score) <= AMBIGUITY_DELTA:
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:300:        return (primary, secondary, scores)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:301:    return (primary, None, scores)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:303:def route_[skill_name]_resources(user_request, task=None):
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:305:    primary, secondary, scores = classify_intents(user_request, task)
.opencode/skills/sk-doc/assets/skill/skill_md_template.md:316:        guarded = _guard_in_skill(relative_path)
