.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:25:- Checking whether a proposed cleanup crosses from documentation/navigation into runtime migration.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:26:- Explaining why memory and advisor processes must not share database write ownership.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:30:Advisor routing is a standalone MCP process boundary; documentation can point across packages, but runtime ownership stays inside `system-skill-advisor`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:34:- `mcp_server/advisor-server.ts`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:42:ADR-001 chooses a standalone MCP server named `mk_skill_advisor`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:51:- Advisor tests, fixtures, playbook and feature catalog.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:60:mk_skill_advisor -> advisor tools and skill graph DB
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/runtime/standalone_mcp_shape.md:64:The memory MCP server may keep a temporary bridge for legacy `advisor_*` calls during migration. It must not remain the long-term owner of advisor implementation modules or database writes.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:22:- Aligning runtime adapters with the native advisor package.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:26:Hooks surface compact advisor context; they do not replace skill loading or leak raw prompt text.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:31:- `mcp_server/lib/skill-advisor-brief.ts`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/hooks/skill_advisor_hook.md:32:- `mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor.py`
