.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:3:description: "Policy for the package-local skill graph SQLite database path required by ADR-001 constraint A."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:5:  - "system skill advisor db path"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:6:  - "skill-graph.sqlite advisor path"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:7:  - "advisor database policy"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:12:Policy for the package-local skill graph SQLite database path required by ADR-001 constraint A.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:20:Defines the package-local SQLite database location for the standalone advisor runtime and documents the allowed test/CI override behavior.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:24:- Verifying where `skill-graph.sqlite` and lease sidecars must live.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:30:The advisor owns its SQLite state inside `system-skill-advisor`; adjacent MCP packages must not become competing writers.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:34:- `mcp_server/lib/skill-graph/skill-graph-db.ts`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:41:The advisor database lives inside the standalone advisor skill package:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:44:.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:50:.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:56:skill-graph.sqlite-wal
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:57:skill-graph.sqlite-shm
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:64:ADR-001 constraint A requires DB-local ownership for the extracted advisor. The database is the advisor's runtime state, so it belongs with the skill that reads, writes, validates and rebuilds it.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:68:- `/doctor:update` and future repair flows can reason per skill package.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:69:- The advisor MCP server can be the single writer for `skill-graph.sqlite`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:70:- `system-spec-kit` keeps memory and spec packet state without owning advisor runtime data.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:71:- Backups, cleanup and integrity checks can target the advisor package directly.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:79:Production and operator docs should treat the package-local path as the default. A runtime override must not be used to silently re-collocate the advisor DB with `system-spec-kit/mcp_server/database/`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:85:Current package state keeps the database under `mcp_server/database/` and exposes it through the standalone `mk_skill_advisor` MCP server.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/config/db_path_policy.md:87:The `skill_graph_*` handlers and the lower-level `lib/skill-graph/` database/query library are advisor-owned and package-local.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:3:description: "How to detect plus reconcile drift between the SQLite skill graph state and the live .opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json source files."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:5:  - "skill graph drift"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:7:  - "skill graph rebuild"
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:13:How to detect plus reconcile drift between the SQLite skill graph state and the live .opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json source files.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:21:Explains how to detect and reconcile drift between SQLite skill graph state and live `graph-metadata.json` source files.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:25:- `advisor_status`, `skill_graph_status` or `skill_graph_validate` reports stale or inconsistent graph state.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:26:- A skill metadata edit is not reflected in query results.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:31:The SQLite graph is rebuildable runtime state; checked-in skill metadata remains the authored source of truth.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:37:- [`skill_graph_query_cookbook.md`](./skill_graph_query_cookbook.md)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:45:1. **Skill added**: a new `.opencode/skills/<name>/graph-metadata.json` appears on disk that the SQLite graph has not indexed yet.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:46:2. **Skill removed**: a skill directory is deleted but the SQLite graph still has rows for it.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:49:5. **Hash drift**: any file under `.opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json` plus `.opencode/skills/*/SKILL.md` changes, computed via SHA-256 hash. The daemon watches for hash changes per `freshness_contract.md` §5.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:55:### Via `skill_graph_status`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:58:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_status({})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:69:### Via `skill_graph_validate`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:72:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_validate({})
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:86:find .opencode/skills -name 'graph-metadata.json' -exec sha256sum {} + | sort
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:89:Compare against the daemon's recorded signature stored alongside `mcp_server/database/.skill-graph.sig`. Mismatches indicate drift.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:98:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_rebuild({ "force": true })
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:108:mcp__mk_skill_advisor__skill_graph_scan({ "skillsRoot": ".opencode/skills" })
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:115:If `advisor_rebuild` plus `skill_graph_scan` both fail:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:120:rm -f .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite{,-wal,-shm}
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:121:rm -f .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/.skill-graph.sig
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:122:rm -f .opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/mcp_server/database/.skill-graph.lease
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:126:After hard reset, verify with `advisor_status` plus `skill_graph_validate` before trusting recommendations.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:134:| Rebuild succeeds but trustState stays stale | Generation counter not bumping | Inspect `advisor_status.generation`. If frozen, kill MCP server plus restart. File a bug if reproducible |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:135:| Source files unreadable (permission error) | `advisor_rebuild` errors with EACCES | Fix filesystem permissions on `.opencode/skills/*/graph-metadata.json`. The daemon needs read access |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:137:| Schema version mismatch (json v2, SQLite expects v1) | Validate reports schema-violation errors for new skills | Run `advisor_rebuild --force`. The rebuild applies any pending schema migrations |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:138:| Hash signature corruption | Daemon refuses to detect drift (signature unreadable) | Delete `.skill-graph.sig`. Daemon regenerates on next scan |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:139:| New skill added but never indexed | `skill_graph_query` returns empty for the new skill | Run `skill_graph_scan` manually. If still missing, verify the new graph-metadata.json passes JSON validation |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:140:| Drift after `git pull` brings new graph-metadata.json files | Common after upstream sync | Run `advisor_rebuild --force` once after `git pull` to re-sync |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:149:- [`skill_graph_query_cookbook.md`](./skill_graph_query_cookbook.md), query the graph after reconciliation
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:150:- [`tool_ids_reference.md`](../runtime/tool_ids_reference.md), `advisor_rebuild`, `skill_graph_scan`, `skill_graph_validate` schemas
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_drift.md:152:- `mcp_server/handlers/skill-graph/scan.ts`, `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-rebuild.ts`, source
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:3:description: "Worked examples for all 10 query types of skill_graph_query: depends_on, dependents, enhances, enhanced_by, family_members, conflicts, transitive_path, hub_skills, orphans, subgraph."
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:5:  - "skill graph query cookbook"
