.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:21:Provides worked examples for every supported `skill_graph_query` query type.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:37:- [`skill_graph_drift.md`](./skill_graph_drift.md)
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:45:| `depends_on` | Outbound dependencies of a skill | §3 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:49:| `family_members` | Sibling skills in the same family | §7 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:51:| `transitive_path` | Path between two skills through edges | §9 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:52:| `hub_skills` | Skills with highest in or out degree | §10 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:54:| `subgraph` | Local neighborhood around a skill | §12 |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:60:**Purpose**: Returns the outbound `depends_on` edges declared in a skill graph-metadata.json `edges.depends_on[]` array.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:65:{ "queryType": "depends_on", "skillId": "system-skill-advisor" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:68:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:73:  "skillId": "system-skill-advisor",
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:78:**Worked example**: `system-skill-advisor` currently has no hard dependencies. Query returns an empty edge list from the source graph-metadata.json.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:80:**Gotcha**: An empty `relationships[]` does not mean the skill has no upstream needs. Many skills rely on `system-spec-kit` implicitly through the validate workflow without declaring it as a hard dependency. Cross-reference with the manual_testing_playbook for the runtime dependency story.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:86:**Purpose**: Reverse query. Returns skills that declare `depends_on` pointing to the queried skill.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:91:{ "queryType": "dependents", "skillId": "system-spec-kit" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:94:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:99:  "skillId": "system-spec-kit",
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:101:    { "source": "sk-code", "weight": 0.8, "context": "validation workflow" },
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:102:    { "source": "sk-doc", "weight": 0.6, "context": "template engine" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:107:**Worked example**: `system-spec-kit` is the platform anchor. Most `sk-*` skills declare it as a dependency. Query returns the full inbound dependency list with each source skill's weight and context.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:115:**Purpose**: Returns outbound `enhances` edges from the queried skill's graph-metadata.json `edges.enhances[]` array.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:120:{ "queryType": "enhances", "skillId": "system-skill-advisor" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:123:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:128:  "skillId": "system-skill-advisor",
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:130:    { "target": "cli-claude-code", "weight": 0.7, "context": "routes claude delegation requests" },
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:131:    { "target": "cli-codex", "weight": 0.7, "context": "routes codex delegation requests" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:136:**Worked example**: The advisor enhances each CLI skill by routing prompts to the right one. Query returns the outbound enhancement edges, each carrying a context string explaining the relationship.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:138:**Gotcha**: Asymmetric `enhances` declarations are common. A skill can declare it enhances another without that other declaring `enhanced_by`. The propagate-enhances internal tool (see [`propagate_enhances.md`](./propagate_enhances.md)) detects and proposes the missing reciprocals.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:144:**Purpose**: Inverse of `enhances`. Returns skills that declare they enhance the queried skill.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:149:{ "queryType": "enhanced_by", "skillId": "sk-code" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:152:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:157:  "skillId": "sk-code",
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:159:    { "source": "system-skill-advisor", "weight": 0.7, "context": "routes implementation requests" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:164:**Worked example**: `sk-code` is enhanced by the advisor that routes implementation prompts to it. Query returns the inbound enhancement edges.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:166:**Gotcha**: The result reflects only declared inbound edges. Run `skill_graph_propagate_enhances` in `report` mode to find skills that should be enhancing this one but have not declared the edge yet.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:172:**Purpose**: Returns all skills sharing the same `family` field in graph-metadata.json.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:180:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:187:    { "skillId": "system-spec-kit", "category": "system" },
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:188:    { "skillId": "system-code-graph", "category": "system" },
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:189:    { "skillId": "system-skill-advisor", "category": "system" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:194:**Worked example**: The `system` family contains the three first-party `system-*` skills. Query returns all members with their categories.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:202:**Purpose**: Returns skills marked as mutually exclusive via `edges.conflicts[]` in graph-metadata.json.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:207:{ "queryType": "conflicts", "skillId": "cli-codex" }
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:210:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:215:  "skillId": "cli-codex",
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:220:**Worked example**: Most cli-* skills do not declare conflicts. They route per dispatch and do not interfere. An empty result is the common case.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:222:**Gotcha**: A non-empty `conflicts[]` signals a skill-level invariant. The advisor will refuse to surface both skills in the same recommendation set when conflicts are declared.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:228:**Purpose**: Finds a path between two skills through any combination of edge types.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:233:{ "queryType": "transitive_path", "from": "system-skill-advisor", "to": "sk-code" }
