.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:280:**Worked example**: `system-spec-kit` is the highest-degree hub because almost every other skill depends on its validation workflow. Use this query to identify high-blast-radius skills before refactors.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:282:**Gotcha**: A high degree count does not mean a skill is high-quality. It just means many other skills point at it. Cross-reference with `advisor_validate` accuracy slices to see whether routing TO this skill is actually high-precision.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:288:**Purpose**: Returns skills with zero edges in either direction.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:296:**Output shape**:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:301:  "skills": []
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:305:**Worked example**: A healthy skill graph has zero orphans. Every skill should declare at least one outbound or inbound edge so the advisor can route to it via graph signals.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:307:**Gotcha**: An orphan skill will still surface in `advisor_recommend` if its explicit_author or lexical lanes score high enough. But the graph_causal lane contribution will be zero. Orphans are a signal to add at least one edge in the skill graph-metadata.json.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/skill_graph_query_cookbook.md:313:**Purpose**: Returns the local neighborhood around a skill (default radius 1, configurable).
