.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:20:Documents the internal `skill_graph_propagate_enhances` tool for detecting and optionally applying missing inbound `enhances` edges.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:30:Enhance-edge propagation is a high-trust authoring helper: report first, write only with explicit trusted-caller intent.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:34:- `mcp_server/handlers/skill-graph/propagate-enhances.ts`
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:41:Three rules contribute to the composite confidence score with capped maximum contributions:
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:45:| family-inference | 0.45 | Source skill already enhances many peers in target's family |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:46:| asset-shape | 0.30 | Target has files or assets matching source's `enhance_when` rules |
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:49:Family-inference is the strongest signal and requires at least three existing `enhances` entries before it contributes. Asset-shape inspects the target skill's filesystem layout against the source's declared trigger shape. Sibling-transitivity walks one hop through known sibling links.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:57:- `report` - Returns candidates without making any changes. This is the default.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:58:- `propose` - Returns candidates without making any changes. Functionally an alias for `report`.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:70:- The workspace-escape guard resolves `skillsRoot` and verifies it stays under the current working directory. External absolute paths are rejected.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:71:- The default mode is `report`. No writes occur unless `mode:'apply'` is set explicitly.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:83:- Maintenance sweeps that discover missing `enhances` relationships across a refactored skill set.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:84:- Authoring assistance after adding a new skill that fits an existing family.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:85:- Validation runs that report candidate edges without writing, so operators can review the proposal before applying.
.opencode/skills/system-skill-advisor/references/graph/propagate_enhances.md:87:The tool sits beside the eight other skill-graph tools as a low-frequency, high-trust authoring helper.
