.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:137:| REQ-005 | README and gemini mirror present | `.opencode/commands/README.txt` lists the new command and lanes; `.gemini/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.toml` exists and mirrors the opencode command |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:138:| REQ-006 | No placeholders remain | All authored command and YAML surfaces use real content; strict validate reports no unfilled template placeholders |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:146:- **SC-001**: A user can start a model-benchmark run from a command and reach benchmark-complete, while the agent-improvement lane behaves exactly as before.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:147:- **SC-002**: Both lanes are discoverable: the advisor routes each command to its skill, and the README plus gemini mirror surface the model-benchmark command.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:157:| Dependency | Model-benchmark runtime contract (phases 003 to 005) | High - no Lane B run without it | Reuse the shipped contract as-is; this phase only wires the command surface |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:158:| Risk | Lane A regression from the additive branch | Med | Keep lane resolution additive; CMD-1 behavioral identity gate confirms Lane A is unchanged |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:168:- Does the dedicated `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command fully replace the lane-asking branch, or do both stay as parallel entries? (Current design: both stay, the branch routes into the same Lane B workflow.)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:177:- **NFR-P01**: The lane-asking branch adds at most one question to the agent-improvement command. It must not add a perceptible startup delay to a Lane A run.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:180:- **NFR-R01**: Lane A behavioral identity is the reliability invariant. Selecting agent-improvement reproduces the pre-phase Lane A workflow with no observable difference.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:181:- **NFR-R02**: Lane B reuses the shipped loop-host contract, so a benchmark run is as reliable as the phase 003 to 005 runtime. This phase adds no new failure modes in the runtime.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:184:- **NFR-S01**: No secrets are introduced into the command, YAMLs, or gemini mirror. Lane B profile and outputs-dir paths stay inside the expected packet-local boundaries.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:193:- User gives no lane signal: the command asks rather than silently defaulting, so Lane B never gets hidden behind an implicit Lane A choice.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:194:- Lane B invoked with no `--profile`: loop-host falls back to the default profile (`assets/benchmark-profiles/default.json`), and the YAML must document that default.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:197:- A Lane B run with `--grader llm` but no reachable executor: the run should surface the dispatch failure rather than silently degrade. The YAML default is `--grader noop` so the happy path is deterministic.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:201:- Lane resolution is a one-time branch per invocation. Once a lane is chosen the run stays in that lane, with no mid-run lane switch.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/spec.md:212:| Risk | 11/25 | The agent-improvement command is a shared live surface; the additive branch must preserve Lane A identity |
