.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:28:# Decision Record: two-lane deep-review remediation
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:45:| **Deciders** | Orchestrator, remediation agent |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:52:The 014 review confirmed F-P0-1: `loop-host.cjs` `parseArgs` only accepts `--key=value` and bare flags, but all three Lane B command surfaces invoke loop-host with SPACE-form flags (`--profile {profile} --scorer {scoring_method} --grader {grader}`), so `profile`, `outputs-dir`, `scorer`, and `grader` all parse to `true`. The model-benchmark command does not run as intended. We could either teach the parser the space-form or rewrite the three command surfaces to `=`-form.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:56:- TST-1 byte-identity gate must hold: the `=`-form parse path and the Lane A plan must be byte-identical pre and post fix.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:89:- The Lane B command runs as intended through the YAML path.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:110:| 1 | **Necessary?** | PASS | P0 release blocker; Lane B is broken without it |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:143:| **Deciders** | Orchestrator, remediation agent |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:150:F-P1-1 found `buildSpawnSpec` runs external model executors with write-capable modes (Claude `--permission-mode acceptEdits`, Codex `--sandbox workspace-write`, Devin `--permission-mode auto`). Grading and benchmarking should observe output, not edit the workspace.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:163:**We chose**: Default grader/executor dispatch to read-only/no-edit modes, with an explicit documented opt-in for write-capable evaluation in an isolated temp workspace, and assert `cwd` stays inside the benchmark sandbox before spawning.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:165:**How it works**: `buildSpawnSpec` emits read-only permission flags per executor by default. A documented opt-in flag or env var switches to write-capable mode only when the caller explicitly requests it, and the spawn path validates the resolved `cwd` is inside the benchmark sandbox first.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:222:- `scripts/model-benchmark/dispatch-model.cjs` `buildSpawnSpec`: read-only default + cwd sandbox assert + opt-in.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:240:| **Deciders** | Orchestrator, remediation agent |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:247:F-P1-9 found fixture-controlled `fixture.id` is used in `path.join(outputsDir, ` + "`${fixture.id}.md`" + `)` without validating it is a basename or that the resolved path stays under `outputsDir`. A crafted id with separators or `..` can read or score files outside the benchmark output directory.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:284:- Fixture ids cannot escape the benchmark output directory.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:318:- `scripts/model-benchmark/run-benchmark.cjs`: fixture-id guard + resolved-inside-outputs assert.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:336:| **Deciders** | Orchestrator, remediation agent |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:343:F-P1-10 found the hardening note says `DEEP_AGENT_ALLOW_CRITERIA_EXEC=0` refuses criteria-driven shell execution, but the gate defaults permissive for backward compatibility. A default-open shell-execution gate is a standing security gap. The 121/004 remediation chose ON-by-default for backward-compat; the 014 review re-flagged it, so this packet revisits the default.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:347:- Existing trusted benchmark profiles may rely on criteria execution and must remain reachable via explicit opt-in.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:424:## ADR-005: Move the score cache packet-local and key it by candidate
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:432:| **Deciders** | Orchestrator, remediation agent |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:439:Two findings target the score cache. F-P1-11: `defaultCacheDir()` stores scores under `os.tmpdir()/deep-agent-improvement-score-cache`, a shared world-writable path that is later trusted before rescoring. F-P1-12: the cache input hash includes candidate content and target path but not `candidatePath` or `baselinePath`, so a cache hit can carry the wrong candidate or baseline path in the result payload.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:444:- Cache hits must not mislabel which candidate or baseline produced the score.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:454:**How it works**: `defaultCacheDir()` resolves under the packet/runtime root with restrictive permissions; reads validate owner and mode and fall back to a miss on mismatch. The cache key hash adds the candidate and baseline paths, so a hit always corresponds to the exact candidate it scored.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:511:- `scripts/agent-improvement/score-candidate.cjs`: packet-local cache dir + owner/mode validation; cache key includes candidate and baseline paths.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:527:| F-P0-1 | P0 | Lane B command flags misparse to booleans | FIXED | ADR-001; space-form parseArgs + test + e2e |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:528:| F-P0-2 | P0 (refuted) | Model benchmark never dispatches a model | DOCUMENT-ACCEPT | Intended deferral (122/007 F-P2-1, arbiter-upheld); default path is fixture scoring with `--grader noop` |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/decision-record.md:530:| F-P1-2 | P1 | Lane B YAML interpolates `{profile}` unquoted | FIXED | Quote or argv-array both Lane B YAMLs |
