.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:53:The skill's references and assets are now organized by lane instead of by function. Anyone opening `references/` or `assets/` sees three subdirs (`agent-improvement/`, `model-benchmark/`, `shared/`) that match the two-lane model, rather than the old function dirs (integration, promotion-gates, scoring, workflow).
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:57:Flattened into lanes (function subdir dropped, filename kept): `agent-improvement/` holds integration_scanning, mirror_drift_policy, profiling_audit_log, candidate_proposal_format, target_onboarding, score_dimensions; `model-benchmark/` holds benchmark_operator_guide, evaluator_contract, mixed_executor_methodology; `shared/` holds loop_protocol, quick_reference, promotion_gate_contract, promotion_rules, rollback_runbook.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:61:`benchmark-profiles/` and `benchmark-fixtures/` moved into `assets/model-benchmark/`; the agent-improvement loop assets (improvement_charter, improvement_config, improvement_config_reference, improvement_strategy, target_manifest.jsonc, target-profiles) moved into `assets/agent-improvement/`. No shared assets exist, so no `shared/` asset subdir was created.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:65:Every consumer of the moved paths was updated: the SKILL.md RESOURCE_MAP, DEFAULT_RESOURCE, and RUNTIME_ASSETS; both Lane B YAMLs and both Lane A YAMLs; both deep commands; README.md; the skill graph-metadata; scripts (run-benchmark default profilesDir, dispatch-model config join, optin-scorer test); the feature catalog and manual testing playbook; reference cross-links; and the benchmark profile's INTERNAL fixtureDir so fixtures resolve from the new location. The moved markdown assets had `../references/` links that broke one dir deeper and were corrected to `../../references/`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:71:| `references/**` | Moved (git mv) | 14 docs flattened into agent-improvement, model-benchmark, shared |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/010-references-assets-lane-reorg/implementation-summary.md:72:| `assets/**` | Moved (git mv) | benchmark assets to model-benchmark, loop assets to agent-improvement |
