.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:2:title: "Implementation Summary: Command lane-asking for the model-benchmark lane"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:3:description: "Phase 008 shipped the two-lane command experience: the agent-improvement command now resolves a use-case lane and a dedicated model-benchmark command plus its workflow YAMLs make Lane B first-class. A latent loop-host arg-forwarding defect was fixed."
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:6:  - "model-benchmark command summary"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:15:    recent_action: "Shipped two-lane commands and fixed loop-host scorer/grader forwarding"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:19:      - ".opencode/commands/deep/start-model-benchmark-loop.md"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:21:      - ".opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/loop-host.cjs"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:53:The model-benchmark lane is now first-class at the command layer. Before this phase the only way to benchmark a model or prompt framework was to call `loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark` by hand, and the `/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` command never asked which use case the operator wanted. Phase 008 closes both gaps.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:55:### Lane resolution in the existing command
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:57:`/deep:start-agent-improvement-loop` gained an additive `lane` resolution. When an agent path is supplied (the normal Lane A invocation) the lane resolves to `agent-improvement` with no new prompt and the command runs exactly as before. A `--lane=model-benchmark` flag or a `--profile` argument routes to Lane B. Only when the lane is genuinely ambiguous (no agent path, no flag, interactive mode) does a new first question `Q(lane)` appear. This preserves CMD-1 behavioral identity for every existing Lane A invocation.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:59:### Dedicated model-benchmark command
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:61:A new `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command is the direct Lane B entry for operators who already know the lane. It gathers Lane B inputs (profile, outputs or spec folder, execution mode, scoring method, grader, optional executor and model) and loads the new Lane B workflow YAMLs. A gemini mirror keeps runtime parity.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:63:### Lane B workflow YAMLs
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:65:`deep_start-model-benchmark-loop_auto.yaml` and `_confirm.yaml` follow the structure of the agent-improvement YAMLs but drop the agent-only steps (scan-integration, generate-profile) and run the model-benchmark pipeline through `loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark` (which runs materialize then run-benchmark), then reduce-state, journal, dashboard, and optional mode-aware promotion.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:67:### loop-host scorer and grader forwarding fix
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:69:Independent verification found a latent defect. `loop-host.cjs` `planInvocation()` never forwarded `--scorer` or `--grader` to `run-benchmark.cjs`, so selecting `5dim` or a `mock` or `llm` grader through any command path was a silent no-op that fell back to `pattern` and `noop`, and the report disagreed with the journal. The fix forwards both flags in the model-benchmark branch only, so Lane A byte-identity (TST-1) is untouched. A regression test now asserts the propagation.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/implementation-summary.md:75:| `.opencode/commands/deep/start-agent-improvement-loop.md` | Modified | Additive lane resolution and Lane B handoff, Lane A unchanged |
