.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/008-command-lane-asking/graph-metadata.json:207:    "causal_summary": "This is **Phase 8** of the two-lane program. The deep-agent-improvement skill already has two runtime lanes: Lane A (agent-improvement, improve an agent `.md` file) and Lane B (model-benchmark, benchmark or optimize a model or prompt framework). Lane B works as a skill mode but has no command entry. This phase makes Lane B first-class at the command layer.",
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:2:title: "shared: Cross-Lane Scripts"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:3:description: "Mode router, promotion, fixtures, state reducer, journal, and coverage scripts serving both deep-agent-improvement lanes."
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:5:  - "shared deep-agent-improvement scripts"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:10:# shared: Cross-Lane Scripts
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:16:`shared/` holds the scripts used by BOTH lanes of the deep-agent-improvement skill: Lane A (agent-improvement) and Lane B (model-benchmark). `loop-host.cjs` is the mode router that dispatches into either lane, and the remaining scripts are lane-agnostic helpers for promotion, fixtures, state reduction, journaling, and coverage tracking.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:20:- `loop-host.cjs` is the single entry point. It reads `--mode` (`agent-improvement` default or `model-benchmark`) and spawns the lane scripts.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:42:│ Lane A names     │  │ shared names      │  │ Lane B names      │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:44:│ improvement/     │  │ materialize, etc. │  │ benchmark/        │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:48:  Lane A names    ───▶ ../agent-improvement/<name>
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:49:  Lane B names    ───▶ ../model-benchmark/<name>
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:60:+-- promote-candidate.cjs               # Mode-aware guarded canonical promotion
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:61:+-- materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs  # Renders benchmark fixtures into outputs dir
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:75:| `promote-candidate.cjs` | Guarded promotion of a candidate to the canonical manifest target. Evaluates weighted-score, benchmark-aggregate, per-dimension, and mirror-sync gates, and refuses promotion while the runtime config is proposal-only. Requires `--approve`. Imports `../lib/promotion-gates.cjs` and `../lib/mirror-sync-verify.cjs`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:76:| `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` | Renders fixtures referenced by a profile into a benchmark outputs directory so scoring sees real inputs. CLI: `--profile <path> --outputs-dir <path>`. Run before `run-benchmark.cjs` in the Lane B plan. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:77:| `reduce-state.cjs` | Reduces the runtime ledger into an experiment registry and dashboard. Buckets records by `mode` (`agent-improvement` vs `model-benchmark`), reports lane mode-mix per profile and globally, evaluates stop status, and renders journal, lineage, coverage, and mirror-sync sections. CLI: `node reduce-state.cjs <improvement-runtime-root>`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:87:| Imports | `promote-candidate.cjs` imports `../lib/promotion-gates.cjs` and `../lib/mirror-sync-verify.cjs`. `loop-host.cjs` resolves lane scripts by path and spawns them with `spawnSync`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:88:| Exports | `loop-host.cjs`, `improvement-journal.cjs`, and `mutation-coverage.cjs` expose named module exports. `loop-host.cjs`, `promote-candidate.cjs`, `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs`, `reduce-state.cjs`, and `improvement-journal.cjs` run as CLI entrypoints. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:89:| Ownership | These scripts serve both lanes. Lane A scripts live in `../agent-improvement/`, Lane B scripts in `../model-benchmark/`. The spawn map keeps bare names in the plan and resolves the lane directory at spawn time. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:111:│ spawnSync each step (Lane A or Lane B)    │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:126:| `loop-host.cjs` | CLI | Mode router. `[--mode=agent-improvement] --candidate=<path>` or `--mode=model-benchmark --profile=<path-or-id> --outputs-dir=<path>`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:127:| `promote-candidate.cjs` | CLI | Guarded promotion with `--approve` and gate-evidence arguments. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/shared/README.md:128:| `materialize-benchmark-fixtures.cjs` | CLI | `--profile <path> --outputs-dir <path>`. |
