.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:3:description: "SKILL.md frames model-benchmark as a bolt-on Mode 4 inside the agent-improvement lane, and the smart-router lacks a clean MODEL_BENCHMARK intent surface. This phase restructures SKILL.md into two co-equal lanes and aligns the router."
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:6:  - "model-benchmark co-equal lane"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:12:    packet_pointer: "skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane"
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:52:| **Handoff Criteria** | SKILL.md presents two co-equal lanes, router carries a MODEL_BENCHMARK intent with a RESOURCE_MAP entry, plus DQI excellent and validate strict pass |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:60:This is **Phase 9** of the two-lane program. Phase 008 made the model-benchmark lane (Lane B) first-class at the command layer (a dedicated `/deep:start-model-benchmark-loop` command, Lane B workflow YAMLs, advisor routing, README). The skill documentation has not caught up: SKILL.md still frames model-benchmark as "Mode 4" bolted onto the end of the agent-improvement lane rather than as a co-equal lane. This phase aligns SKILL.md and the smart-router with the two co-equal lanes the command layer already ships.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:66:- The model-benchmark runtime contract from phases 003 to 005 (`loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark`, scorers, mode-aware records). SKILL.md describes it, it does not change it.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:69:- A two-co-equal-lane structure in SKILL.md: Lane A (agent-improvement) and Lane B (model-benchmark) as peer sections, not a Mode 4 bolt-on.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:70:- A MODEL_BENCHMARK intent in the smart-router with a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:83:SKILL.md frames the model-benchmark lane as "Mode 4: Model-Benchmark" appended inside the agent-improvement lane section (§3), even though §1 already declares two co-equal lanes and points Lane B at a §4 that is actually Success Criteria. The smart-router has a MODEL_BENCHMARK intent entry but it sits beside agent-improvement intents without being surfaced as a co-equal lane. A reader sees model-benchmark as a sub-mode of agent-improvement, which contradicts the command layer that already ships two co-equal entry points. The skill documentation and the shipped command surfaces disagree about whether model-benchmark is a lane or a mode.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:86:Restructure SKILL.md so model-benchmark is a co-equal lane with agent-improvement (not a Mode 4 bolt-on), fix the internal lane cross-references, and confirm the smart-router carries a MODEL_BENCHMARK intent with a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry, so the skill documentation matches the two-lane reality the command layer already ships.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:95:- Lift the "Mode 4: Model-Benchmark" content out of the agent-improvement lane section and present Lane A (agent-improvement) and Lane B (model-benchmark) as co-equal peer sections.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:96:- Fix the §1 "Lane B is detailed in §N" cross-reference so it points at the real Lane B section.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:97:- Keep the smart-router MODEL_BENCHMARK intent and confirm it has a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:103:- The agent "Mode awareness" to "Lane awareness" note across runtime mirrors - that is phase 011.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:110:| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/SKILL.md` | Modify | Restructure into two co-equal lanes, fix lane cross-references, confirm MODEL_BENCHMARK router intent plus RESOURCE_MAP entry |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:122:| REQ-001 | Two co-equal lanes present | SKILL.md presents Lane A (agent-improvement) and Lane B (model-benchmark) as peer sections, and model-benchmark is no longer framed as a Mode 4 sub-mode of the agent-improvement lane |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:123:| REQ-002 | Router MODEL_BENCHMARK intent present | The smart-router carries a MODEL_BENCHMARK intent with a matching RESOURCE_MAP entry, so model-benchmark routing is a first-class router key |
