.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:130:| REQ-004 | DQI excellent | sk-doc DQI score for SKILL.md is excellent (>=90) |
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:140:- **SC-001**: A reader of SKILL.md sees agent-improvement and model-benchmark as two co-equal lanes, matching the two command entry points shipped in phase 008.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:141:- **SC-002**: The smart-router routes a model-benchmark task through a MODEL_BENCHMARK intent with its own RESOURCE_MAP entry, and SKILL.md passes DQI excellent plus strict validate with no placeholders.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:161:- Should Lane B get a full peer section with its own numbered modes, or a tighter co-equal section that defers shared runtime contracts to the common sections? (Current design: a co-equal Lane B section that reuses the shared runtime-contract sections.)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:162:- Does the smart-router need any new RESOURCE_MAP target beyond the existing benchmark operator guide and evaluator contract? (Current design: reuse the existing MODEL_BENCHMARK RESOURCE_MAP entry, and add a target only if a Lane B reader would otherwise miss guidance.)
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:171:- **NFR-P01**: The router restructure must not add a new always-loaded resource. MODEL_BENCHMARK stays a conditional intent so a Lane A task does not pay for Lane B guidance.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:174:- **NFR-R01**: The agent-improvement lane guidance stays intact. A reader following Lane A reaches the same runtime contracts and rules as before the restructure.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:175:- **NFR-R02**: The smart-router pseudocode stays internally consistent. INTENT_SIGNALS, RESOURCE_MAP, and any keyword lists agree on the MODEL_BENCHMARK key.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:187:- A task that mentions both "improve an agent" and "benchmark a model": the router may select both intents under its ambiguity rule, so the two-lane structure must let a reader follow either lane without cross-contamination.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/spec.md:191:- A RESOURCE_MAP entry that points at a missing reference: the existence-check-before-load guard skips it. The MODEL_BENCHMARK entry must point at references that exist before this phase reorganizes them in phase 010.
