.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/015-fix-deep-review-findings-for-two-lane-code/graph-metadata.json:204:    "causal_summary": "The 014 two-lane deep review returned a CONDITIONAL verdict against the two-lane program (121/008-013). This packet remediates every active finding: 1 confirmed P0 (the Lane B command flags misparse to booleans because `loop-host.cjs` `parseArgs` does not accept space-form flags), a cluster of 16 P1 findings (security: write-capable grader dispatch, unquoted shell interpolation, fixture-id traversal, open-by-default criteria-exec, shared-tmp score cache; traceability: invalid outcomes, dropped executor fields, missing provenance, overwritten reports, non-packet-local pause state, a Lane A-referencing promotion gate, split config, stale agent-note paths), and 16 P2 advisories. Each finding gets exactly one disposition - FIXED with a test or adversarial check where applicable, or DOCUMENT-ACCEPT with rationale. The work preserves TST-1 byte-identity in `scripts/shared/loop-host.cjs` and keeps the vitest suite green.",
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/017-two-lane-opus-deep-review/plan.md:3:description: "Run the deep-review loop (Opus 4.8, native executor, workflow format) over the curated post-015 two-lane code: confirm remediations hold, hunt new issues, emit an adjudicated review-report."
