.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/plan.md:82:- **Smart-router intent map**: INTENT_SIGNALS and RESOURCE_MAP carry a MODEL_BENCHMARK key whose resources exist, kept internally consistent after the restructure.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/009-skill-md-two-lane/plan.md:85:A reader or the router enters SKILL.md, sees two co-equal lanes in §1, and follows either Lane A or Lane B. The router scores intents, selects MODEL_BENCHMARK for benchmark-phrased tasks, and loads the matching RESOURCE_MAP entry. Lane-specific guidance loads only when its intent matches, while shared runtime contracts stay available to both lanes.
