.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:32:- File: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs:101`
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:33:- Evidence: `scoreAcceptanceDeterministic()` accepts `criteria.acceptance` as data, then for `type === 'deterministic'` runs `execSync(a.command, { cwd: cwdAbs, ... })` without a command allowlist or argv splitting. The ported D2 bundle gate repeats the same pattern by selecting a `smoke-run` or `deterministic` acceptance command and executing `execSync(acceptance.command, ...)` in `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scorer/deterministic/bundle-gate.cjs:128` and `:153`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:34:- Evidence: The same scorer path only requires `cwd` to be absolute at `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs:172`; grep criteria then use `path.join(cwdAbs, a.file)` at `:82` and `:95`, so `../` segments can resolve outside the intended fixture workspace.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:35:- Claim: Any benchmark profile or caller that can supply `criteria.acceptance` can run shell commands under the local agent process and can probe paths outside the fixture cwd.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:36:- Counterevidence sought: Direct CLI model dispatch in `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/dispatch-model.cjs:173` uses `spawnSync(spec.bin, spec.args, ...)`, and the executor specs build argv arrays instead of shell strings. That rules out shell injection in `prompt/model/agent` dispatch args, but it does not cover the scorer acceptance-command path.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:37:- Alternative explanation: These criteria may be intended as trusted local fixtures only. That downgrades from P0, but the benchmark mode is explicitly a reusable scoring surface and the reviewed code has no guard that enforces trusted fixture provenance.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:40:- Downgrade trigger: Downgrade to P2 only if benchmark profiles are cryptographically pinned or otherwise proven to be repo-owned trusted code, and the scorer API is not reachable with user-provided criteria.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:43:#### DR-003-P1-002 - D4 grader accepts unbounded model-provided scores and can poison benchmark integrity
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:45:- File: `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scorer/grader/harness.cjs:63`
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:46:- Evidence: `parseGraderResponse()` accepts any numeric `score` from strict JSON at `:67-69`, fenced JSON at `:78-80`, regex-extracted JSON at `:89-91`, and finally accepts a score-only regex via `parseFloat()` at `:98-105`. None of these paths enforce finite numbers or a `0..1` range.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:47:- Evidence: The parsed `grader.score` is used directly as D4 in `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scorer/score-model-variant.cjs:216`, then multiplied into the weighted score at `:220-221`. The result is also cached and reused via `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/scorer/grader/harness.cjs:191`.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:48:- Claim: A malformed or adversarial grader response can inflate scores above the rubric range, poison the grader cache, and make benchmark promotion decisions trust invalid model output.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:49:- Counterevidence sought: Mock paths return in-range scores, and the system prompt asks for JSON only. No schema validation or clamp exists in the code path that consumes real grader output.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:50:- Alternative explanation: The grader model is operator-controlled rather than attacker-controlled. That limits exploitability, but this is still an integrity boundary because the benchmark relies on LLM output as a scoring input.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:53:- Downgrade trigger: Downgrade to P2 if a caller outside this scope validates grader output before `score-model-variant.cjs` consumes it, or if real grader mode is permanently disabled in benchmark mode.
.opencode/specs/skilled-agent-orchestration/121-deep-agent-improvement-benchmark-mode/007-benchmark-mode-hardening-review/review/iterations/iteration-003.md:54:- Recommendation: Validate with a strict schema, require `Number.isFinite(score) && score >= 0 && score <= 1`, reject score-only fallback for promotion-grade runs, and avoid caching invalid parse results as reusable grader outputs.
