.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:20:  "adversarial_findings": ["additional concerns beyond the score itself"],
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:27:Default to suspicion. Score generously (high score) ONLY if you can affirmatively verify every claim. If you can't verify a symbol exists, treat it as suspicious. Your job is to surface what the primary grader might have missed because it was fluency-tuned to reward plausible-looking output.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/prompts/system-skeptic.md:37:If your score differs from the primary grader's by more than 0.15, the harness will flag this as a dispute. Provide explicit evidence so the operator can adjudicate.
