.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:2:title: "agent-improvement: Lane A Scripts"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:3:description: "Lane A (agent-improvement) scoring, profiling, lineage, and integration scripts for the deep-agent-improvement skill."
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:6:  - "score-candidate"
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:10:# agent-improvement: Lane A Scripts
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:16:`agent-improvement/` holds the Lane A (agent-improvement) scripts. Lane A evaluates and improves an agent file: it builds a dynamic profile of the target agent, scores a candidate across five dimensions, scans integration surfaces, and produces lineage, drift, trade-off, and stability reporting.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:20:- `score-candidate.cjs` is the lane entrypoint. `shared/loop-host.cjs` spawns it in agent-improvement mode.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:21:- `score-candidate.cjs` spawns `scan-integration.cjs` and `generate-profile.cjs` per scored candidate.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:22:- All files import shared helpers from `../lib/` (`typed-errors.cjs`, `promotion-gates.cjs`).
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:23:- `candidate-lineage.cjs`, `trade-off-detector.cjs`, and `benchmark-stability.cjs` are library modules with named exports, not CLI entrypoints.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:31:│                      agent-improvement (Lane A)                    │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:35:│ shared/loop-host │ ───▶ │ score-candidate.cjs      │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:50:                │ promotion-gates    │
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:53:Dependency direction: loop-host ───▶ score-candidate ───▶ generate-profile + scan-integration ───▶ ../lib
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:62:+-- score-candidate.cjs       # Lane entrypoint: dynamic 5-dimension scorer
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:67:+-- benchmark-stability.cjs   # Library: score variance + weight advisory
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:68:+-- check-mirror-drift.cjs    # CLI: canonical-to-mirror drift report
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:79:| `score-candidate.cjs` | Lane entrypoint. Reads candidate (and optional baseline), spawns `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs`, scores structural, ruleCoherence, integration, outputQuality, and systemFitness dimensions, applies weights and promotion gates, caches by input hash, and emits a `scored` result with `mode: 'agent-improvement'`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:84:| `benchmark-stability.cjs` | Library exports (`measureStability`, `stabilityCoefficient`, `generateWeightRecommendations`, and related) reporting score variance and weight-optimization advisories. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:85:| `check-mirror-drift.cjs` | CLI reporting drift between a canonical agent body and its mirrors. Args include `--output`, `--canonical`, `--mirrors`, `--manifest`. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:94:| Imports | May import `../lib/*` (`typed-errors.cjs`, `promotion-gates.cjs`). `score-candidate.cjs` spawns sibling `generate-profile.cjs` and `scan-integration.cjs` as child processes. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:95:| Exports | `candidate-lineage.cjs`, `trade-off-detector.cjs`, and `benchmark-stability.cjs` expose named module exports. `score-candidate.cjs`, `generate-profile.cjs`, `scan-integration.cjs`, `check-mirror-drift.cjs`, and `rollback-candidate.cjs` run `main()` as CLI entrypoints. |
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/README.md:96:| Ownership | Lane A owns agent-file evaluation and improvement. Lane B model-benchmark scripts live in `../model-benchmark/`. Cross-lane and shared scripts live in `../shared/`. |
