.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/agent-improvement/scan-integration.cjs:2:// ║ Integration Surface Scanner for deep-agent-improvement                      ║
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:16:`grader/` owns the D4 hallucination dimension. `harness.cjs` builds the grader prompt, dispatches it, parses the JSON response, clamps the score, and caches the result. `dispute.cjs` decides when to escalate to an adversarial second call.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:20:- The grader is pluggable. `score-model-variant.cjs` builds a grader function for `noop`, `mock`, or `llm` (real) modes, and the harness runs the mock or real dispatch path.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:21:- The model-provided score and confidence are clamped to `[0,1]`, including on the cache-hit path, so a malformed response cannot poison the weighted total.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:22:- Parsing falls back through fenced JSON, regex object extraction, and a score-only regex before reporting `parse_status: failed`.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:30:score-model-variant.cjs (buildGraderFn)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/model-benchmark/scorer/grader/README.md:70:| `dispute.cjs` | Exports `shouldEscalateToDualGrader`, `adversarialSecondCall`, and `dualGraderInvocation`. Escalates when the last call confidence is below the threshold or the recent dispute rate exceeds the threshold, then runs a second `gradeD4` with `prompts/system-skeptic.md` and reports median, delta, and a dispute flag. |
