     9	
    10	# Documentation Creation Specialist - Unified Markdown & Component Management
    11	
    12	Unified specialist providing: (1) Document quality pipeline with structure enforcement and content optimization, (2) OpenCode component creation (skills, agents, commands) with scaffolding, validation and packaging, (3) ASCII flowchart creation for visualizing workflows, (4) Install guide creation for setup documentation and (5) Feature catalog and manual testing playbook creation for inventory and validation packages.
    13	
    14	**Core Principle**: Structure first, then content, then quality.
    15	
    16	**Architecture**: Scripts handle deterministic parsing/metrics. AI handles quality judgment and recommendations.
    17	
    18	## 1. WHEN TO USE
    19	
    20	### Use Case: Document Quality Management
    21	
    22	Enforce markdown structure, optimize content for AI assistants, validate quality through script-assisted AI analysis.
    23	
    24	**README Creation** - Use `readme_template.md` + `readme_creation.md` when:
    25	- Creating new README for any folder or project
    26	- User requests "create a README", "add documentation", "write a README"
    27	- Folder needs comprehensive documentation
    28	- Workflow: [readme_creation.md](./references/readme_creation.md) | Template: [readme_template.md](./assets/readme/readme_template.md)
    29	
    30	**Skill README Creation** - Use `skill_readme_template.md` when:
    31	- Creating or refreshing `.opencode/skills/[skill-name]/README.md`
    32	- A skill README needs human-facing purpose, quick start, structure, examples, troubleshooting, FAQ or related-resource navigation
    33	- Template: [skill_readme_template.md](./assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md)
    34	
    35	**Frontmatter Validation** - Use `frontmatter_templates.md` when:
    36	- Validating YAML frontmatter in any document
    37	- Checking required fields for document types
    38	- Fixing frontmatter syntax errors
    39	
    40	**Changelog & Release Notes** - Use `changelog_template.md` when:
    41	- Authoring a global component changelog at `.opencode/changelog/{NN--component}/v{VERSION}.md`
    42	- Composing GitHub release notes that mirror the changelog body
    43	- Choosing between compact (under 10 changes) and expanded (10+ changes or major) formats
    44	- Template: [changelog_template.md](./assets/changelog_template.md). Used by `/create:changelog` (auto + confirm). Nested packet-local changelogs use the spec-kit templates at `.opencode/skills/system-spec-kit/templates/changelog/` instead.
    45	
    46	**Validation Workflow** - Apply after Write/Edit operations:
    47	- Auto-correct filename violations (ALL CAPS to lowercase, hyphens to underscores)
    48	- Fix safe violations (separators, H2 case)
    49	- Check critical violations (missing frontmatter, wrong section order)
    50	
    51	**Manual Optimization** - Run when:
    52	- README needs optimization for AI assistants
    53	- Creating critical documentation (specs, knowledge, skills)
    54	- Pre-release quality checks
    55	- Generating llms.txt for LLM navigation
    56	
    57	### Use Case: OpenCode Component Creation
    58	
    59	Create and manage OpenCode components (skills, agents, commands). Each component type has templates and validation with quality standards.
    60	
    61	**Component Types:**
    62	- **Skills** (.opencode/skills/) - Knowledge bundles with workflows → [skill_creation.md](./references/skill_creation.md)
    63	- **Agents** (.opencode/agents/) - AI personas with tool permissions → [agent_creation.md](./references/agent_creation.md)
    64	- **Commands** (.opencode/commands/) - Slash commands for user invocation → [command_template.md](./assets/command_template.md)
    65	
    66	For larger skills, split deep content into focused reference files and keep concise navigation in `SKILL.md` or `README.md`. When a skill has both cross-cutting standards and document-family guides, prefer `references/global/` for shared rules and the `references/` root for creation-specific workflows.
    67	
    68	Start with: [skill_creation.md](./references/skill_creation.md) (Section 9)
    69	Primary templates:
    70	- [skill_md_template.md](./assets/skill/skill_md_template.md)
    71	- [skill_readme_template.md](./assets/skill/skill_readme_template.md)
    72	- [skill_reference_template.md](./assets/skill/skill_reference_template.md)
    73	- [skill_asset_template.md](./assets/skill/skill_asset_template.md)
    74	
    75	**Use when**:
    76	- User requests skill creation ("create a skill", "make a new skill")
    77	- User requests agent creation ("create an agent", "make a new agent")
    78	- User requests command creation ("create a command", "add a slash command")
    79	- Scaffolding component structure
    80	- Validating component quality
    81	- Packaging skill for distribution
    82	
    83	**Skill Process (6 steps)**: Understanding (examples) → Planning (resources) → Initialization (`init_skill.py`) → Editing (populate) → Packaging (`package_skill.py`) → Iteration (test/improve)
    84	
    85	**Agent Process**: Load `agent_creation.md` and `agent_template.md` → Define frontmatter (mode, permissions) → Create sections (workflow, capabilities, anti-patterns) → Validate → Test
    86	
    87	**Command Process**: Load `command_template.md` → Define frontmatter (name, description) → Create execution logic → Add to command registry → Test
    88	
    89	### Use Case: Flowchart Creation
    90	
    91	Create ASCII flowcharts for visualizing workflows, user journeys and decision trees.
    92	
    93	For styled HTML visuals (interactive diagrams, dashboard pages, or polished data-table renders), use a dedicated HTML workflow instead of forcing ASCII or markdown flowcharts.
    94	
    95	**Use when**:
    96	- Documenting multi-step processes with branching
    97	- Creating decision trees with multiple outcomes
    98	- Showing parallel execution with sync points
    99	- Visualizing approval gates and revision cycles
   100	
   101	**See**: [assets/flowcharts/](./assets/flowcharts/)
   102	
   103	### Use Case: Install Guide Creation
   104	
   105	Create and validate installation documentation for MCP servers, plugins and tools using phase-based templates.
   106	
   107	**Use when**:
   108	- Creating documentation for MCP server installation
   109	- Documenting plugin setup procedures
   110	- Standardizing tool installation across platforms
   111	- Need phase-based validation checkpoints
   112	
   113	**5-Phase Process**: Overview → Prerequisites → Installation → Configuration → Verification
   114	
   115	**See**: [install_guide_creation.md](./references/install_guide_creation.md)
   116	
   117	### Use Case: Manual Testing Playbook Creation
   118	
   119	Create manual testing playbooks with deterministic scenarios, structured evidence collection, and multi-agent execution planning.
   120	
   121	**Manual Testing Playbook** - Use `testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_template.md` when:
   122	- Creating manual testing scenarios for a skill
   123	- Standardizing test evidence and verdict criteria
   124	- Setting up multi-agent test execution planning
   125	
   126	**Canonical Package**: Root `manual_testing_playbook.md` plus numbered category folders with one per-feature file per feature ID.
   127	
   128	**See**:
   129	- [manual_testing_playbook_creation.md](./references/manual_testing_playbook_creation.md)
   130	- [manual_testing_playbook_template.md](./assets/testing_playbook/manual_testing_playbook_template.md)
   131	
   132	### Use Case: Feature Catalog Creation
   133	
   134	Create feature catalogs with a rooted feature inventory, numbered category sections, and per-feature reference files.
   135	
   136	**Feature Catalog** - Use `assets/feature_catalog/feature_catalog_template.md` when:
   137	- Creating a canonical current-state feature inventory for a skill or system
   138	- Linking manual playbooks back to a stable feature reference
   139	- Documenting current behavior with source-file anchors and stable slugs
   140	
   141	**Canonical Package**: Root `FEATURE_CATALOG.md` plus numbered category folders with one per-feature file per catalog entry.
   142	
   143	**See**:
   144	- [feature_catalog_creation.md](./references/feature_catalog_creation.md)
   145	- [feature_catalog_template.md](./assets/feature_catalog/feature_catalog_template.md)
   146	
   147	### Use Case: Benchmark Folder Creation
   148	
   149	Create skill-local `mcp_server/benchmarks/benchmark-<YYYY-MM-DD>/` folders that promote curated bake-off results from an originating spec packet into the consuming skill, where operators reading the MCP code can find the headline without leaving the skill tree.
   150	
   151	**Benchmark Creation** - Use `benchmark_report_template.md` plus `source_template.md` when:
   152	- An ADR or spec packet has just promoted a non-trivial default change (embedder swap, reranker change, retrieval policy) backed by measured evidence
   153	- The originating spec packet has a stable headline plus replay commands and is worth surfacing inside the consuming skill
   154	- A sibling skill already ships a `mcp_server/benchmarks/` folder and parity matters for operators moving between skills
   155	
   156	**Canonical Package**: One `benchmark-<YYYY-MM-DD>/` folder per run, holding `benchmark_report.md` (ten-section curated narrative), `SOURCE.md` (wayfinding pointer back to the spec packet), `results.csv`, `*.jsonl` per-probe data, and optional sidecars (`runtime-measurements.md`, `risk-analysis-*.md`).
   157	
   158	**See**:
   159	- [benchmark_creation.md](./references/benchmark_creation.md)
   160	- [benchmark_report_template.md](./assets/benchmark/benchmark_report_template.md)
   161	- [source_template.md](./assets/benchmark/source_template.md)
   162	
   163	### When NOT to Use (All Modes)
   164	
   165	- Non-markdown files (only `.md` supported)
   166	- Simple typo fixes (use Edit tool directly)
   167	- Internal notes or drafts
   168	- Auto-generated API docs
   169	- Short 2-3 step processes (use bullet points)
   170	
   171	---
   172	
   173	## 2. SMART ROUTING
   174	
   175	> Pattern: see [sk-doc smart-router resilience template](./assets/skill/skill_smart_router.md).
   176	
   177	### Resource Domains
   178	
   179	The router discovers markdown resources recursively from `references/` and `assets/` and then applies intent scoring from `RESOURCE_MAP`. Keep this section domain-focused rather than static file inventories.
