    10	
    11	# Validation Baselines + Troubleshooting
    12	
    13	Baseline metrics for advisor_validate (corpus, holdout, UNKNOWN, daemon, cache latency) plus the troubleshooting playbook when a slice regresses.
    14	
    15	---
    16	
    17	## 1. OVERVIEW
    18	
    19	### Purpose
    20	
    21	Captures `advisor_validate` baseline metrics and the troubleshooting playbook for validation slice regressions.
    22	
    23	### When to Use
    24	
    25	- Running release validation after scorer, metadata or graph changes.
    26	- Diagnosing corpus, holdout, parity, safety or latency failures.
    27	- Deciding whether a lane-weight change can ship.
    28	
    29	### Core Principle
    30	
    31	Validation baselines are the promotion gate for routing behavior changes, not after-the-fact reporting.
    32	
    33	### Key Sources
    34	
    35	- [`lane_weight_tuning.md`](./lane_weight_tuning.md)
    36	- [`advisor_scorer.md`](./advisor_scorer.md)
    37	- [`tool_ids_reference.md`](../runtime/tool_ids_reference.md)
    38	
    39	---
    40	
    41	## 2. CURRENT BASELINES
    42	
    43	Baseline numbers as of remediation SHA `97a318d83`:
    44	
    45	| Metric | Baseline | Source |
    46	|---|---:|---|
    47	| Full-corpus top-1 accuracy | 80.5% | `mcp_server/tests/scorer/corpus.vitest.ts` |
    48	| Holdout top-1 accuracy | 77.5% | `mcp_server/tests/scorer/holdout.vitest.ts` |
    49	| UNKNOWN count (full corpus) | <= 10 | `advisor_validate` `telemetry.unknownCount` |
    50	| Python regression suite | full pass | `mcp_server/scripts/skill_advisor_regression.py` |
    51	| Advisor vitest tests | 167 across 23 files | `mcp_server/tests/` |
    52	| Watcher idle CPU | 0.031% | `mcp_server/lib/daemon/watcher.ts` benchmark |
    53	| Watcher idle RSS | 5.516 MB | same |
    54	| Cache-hit p95 latency | ~6.989 ms | `mcp_server/bench/cache-latency.bench.ts` |
    55	| Uncached p95 latency | ~11.45 ms | same |
    56	
    57	Drift threshold: top-1 accuracy below 80.5% on full corpus OR below 77.5% on holdout is a hard regression that blocks ship.
    58	
    59	---
    60	
    61	## 3. RUNNING VALIDATE
    62	
    63	`advisor_validate` is a heavy operation. It runs the full corpus plus holdout plus parity plus safety plus latency slices in one pass. Require `confirmHeavyRun=true` to invoke.
    64	
    65	```text
    66	mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate({ "confirmHeavyRun": true })
    67	```
    68	
    69	For a single-skill check (skip corpus + holdout):
    70	
    71	```text
    72	mcp__mk_skill_advisor__advisor_validate({ "confirmHeavyRun": true, "skillSlug": "sk-code" })
    73	```
    74	
    75	Response fields to retain for baseline tracking:
    76	
    77	- `overallAccuracy` (float 0..1)
    78	- `slices.corpus.topOne` (float)
    79	- `slices.holdout.topOne` (float)
    80	- `slices.parity.passed` (boolean)
    81	- `slices.safety.violations` (integer count)
    82	- `slices.latency.cacheHitP95Ms` (float)
    83	- `telemetry.unknownCount` (integer)
    84	- `telemetry.lanesDominantCount` (object keyed by lane)
    85	- `perSkill[]` (array of per-skill results)
    86	- `generatedAt` (ISO timestamp)
    87	
    88	---
    89	
    90	## 4. INTERPRETING SLICES
    91	
    92	### Corpus slice
    93	
    94	Runs every skill in the full corpus through the scorer. Top-1 accuracy is the percent of prompts where the correct skill ranks first. Baseline 80.5%.
    95	
    96	Drift signal: a drop of more than 2 percentage points. Likely causes are scorer weight changes, new skills disrupting the lexical lane or stale skill metadata.
    97	
    98	### Holdout slice
    99	
   100	Runs a curated subset reserved for measuring generalization. Top-1 accuracy is the percent where the correct skill ranks first. Baseline 77.5%.
   101	
   102	Drift signal: drop > 1pp is a stronger regression signal than the corpus slice because holdout is unseen during weight tuning.
   103	
   104	### Parity slice
   105	
   106	Checks that the Python shim plus the native MCP scorer return the same recommendations for the same prompt. Pass means parity holds.
   107	
   108	Drift signal: any parity failure. Indicates a divergence between native plus Python paths. Inspect the failing prompt to identify which path drifted.
   109	
   110	### Safety slice
   111	
   112	Checks that prompt-safety boundaries hold. Counts violations where attribution leaks prompt content or trust-state leaks raw input.
   113	
   114	Drift signal: any violation count above zero. Block ship until investigated.
   115	
   116	### Latency slice
   117	
   118	Reports cache-hit p95 plus uncached p95. Baselines: ~6.989 ms cache-hit, ~11.45 ms uncached.
   119	
   120	Drift signal: cache-hit > 15 ms or uncached > 25 ms. Likely causes are SQLite contention, daemon lease starvation or scoring algorithm changes.
   121	
   122	---
   123	
   124	## 5. TROUBLESHOOTING
   125	
   126	| Symptom | Likely Cause | Remediation |
   127	|---|---|---|
   128	| Corpus top-1 drops > 2pp | Scorer weight change OR new skill metadata regression | Run `advisor_rebuild --force`. If still regressed, inspect `perSkill[]` for the regressed skills. Roll back weights per `lane_weight_tuning.md` §6 |
   129	| Holdout top-1 drops while corpus stays steady | Overfit to corpus | Inspect which holdout prompts misroute. Add representative cases to corpus. Re-run tuning |
   130	| UNKNOWN count spikes above 10 | Trust-state went to `absent` OR scorer threshold misconfigured | Check `advisor_status.trustState`. If `absent`, run `advisor_rebuild`. If `live`, inspect lane weights for an over-aggressive threshold |
   131	| Parity slice fails on specific skill | Python shim missing recent token boost added to native scorer | Re-sync `scripts/skill_advisor.py` against `mcp_server/lib/scorer/lanes/` |
   132	| Safety violations > 0 | Attribution leaks prompt content | Inspect `slices.safety.violations[]` for the leaking field. Patch handler to redact |
   133	| Cache-hit p95 > 15 ms | SQLite contention | Check `advisor_status.daemon.leaseHolder`. If contested, kill stale processes. Verify `mcp_server/database/skill-graph.sqlite` integrity |
   134	| Uncached p95 > 25 ms | Scoring algorithm changed OR semantic_shadow lane embedding lookup slow | Profile via `mcp_server/bench/`. If semantic_shadow is the culprit, verify embeddings index freshness |
   135	| `advisor_validate` errors with `confirmHeavyRun is required` | Caller did not opt in | Pass `confirmHeavyRun: true` |
   136	| `advisor_validate` hangs > 5 min | Daemon lock OR test-corpus growth | Check process via `ps`. If hung, kill the MCP server plus restart. If completion exceeds 5 min routinely, trim test corpus or split into incremental runs |
   137	
   138	---
   139	
   140	## 6. RELATED
   141	
   142	- [`tool_ids_reference.md`](../runtime/tool_ids_reference.md) §2, `advisor_validate` input plus output schema
   143	- [`lane_weight_tuning.md`](./lane_weight_tuning.md), when plus how to change lane weights
   144	- [`advisor_scorer.md`](./advisor_scorer.md), scorer mechanics that the validate slices probe
   145	- [`freshness_contract.md`](../runtime/freshness_contract.md), trust state affects validate outcomes
   146	- `feature_catalog/feature_catalog.md` §1, canonical baseline source
   147	- `mcp_server/handlers/advisor-validate.ts`, handler implementation
   148	- `mcp_server/bench/`, latency benchmark harnesses

