    56	<!-- ANCHOR:phase-context -->
    57	## Phase Context
    58	
    59	This is **Phase 3** of packet 121 (add a model-benchmark mode to deep-agent-improvement). It executes the build-delta produced by phase 002's MiniMax M2.7 deep research (canonical source: `../002-implementation-deep-research/research/research.md`, §10 Build-delta). Phase 001 holds the architecture ADRs; this phase implements them.
    60	
    61	**Scope Boundary**: Implement the mode inside `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/` (+ a ported, decoupled scorer). Do NOT change the 120/003 rig (port source) or add new benchmark fixtures beyond what wiring needs.
    62	
    63	**Dependencies**:
    64	- 002 research.md (verified build-delta) + 001 ADRs
    65	- 120/003 `eval-rig/` + `eval-loop/scripts/dispatch-minimax.cjs`, `score-variant.cjs`, grader `harness.cjs` (port source)
    66	
    67	**Deliverables**:
    68	- `loop-host.cjs` (mode-switching entry point), `dispatch-model.cjs` (generic dispatcher), a decoupled scorer behind the scorer seam, mode-aware records + promotion, and the TST-1 identity test.
    69	
    70	**Changelog**:
    71	- When this phase closes, refresh the matching file in ../changelog/ using the parent packet number plus this phase folder name.
    72	<!-- /ANCHOR:phase-context -->
    73	
    74	---
    75	
    76	<!-- ANCHOR:problem -->
    77	## 2. PROBLEM & PURPOSE
    78	
    79	### Problem Statement
    80	deep-agent-improvement can improve agent definitions but cannot benchmark models/prompts; the 120/003 benchmark rig is packet-local and one-off. The 001 design + 002 research define how to add a `model-benchmark` mode, but the code does not exist yet.
    81	
    82	### Purpose
    83	Ship a working `model-benchmark` mode alongside `agent-improvement`, sharing the three seams, with the existing agent-improvement path provably unchanged (byte-for-byte) when mode is unset.
    84	<!-- /ANCHOR:problem -->
    85	
    86	---
    87	
    88	<!-- ANCHOR:scope -->
    89	## 3. SCOPE
    90	
    91	### In Scope
    92	- New `loop-host.cjs` mode-switching entry point (default = agent-improvement)
    93	- New `dispatch-model.cjs` (generalized from `dispatch-minimax.cjs`; executor-routing map)
    94	- Ported, decoupled scorer behind the scorer seam (+ `buildGraderFn(mode)` factory)
    95	- `mode` field on all state records; mode-aware `promote-candidate.cjs`; `reduce-state.cjs` metadata pass-through
    96	- Backward-compat tests (TST-1 identity gate + TST-2..6) and the EC-1..10 edge cases
    97	
    98	### Out of Scope
    99	- Changing the 120/003 rig (port source only) - it stays as the reference
   100	- New benchmark fixtures/profiles beyond wiring needs - separate concern
   101	- Re-deciding architecture (001 ADRs stand) - this is execution
   102	
   103	### Files to Change
   104	
   105	| File Path | Change Type | Description |
   106	|-----------|-------------|-------------|
   107	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/loop-host.cjs` | Create | Mode-switching entry point |
   108	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/dispatch-model.cjs` | Create | Generic model dispatcher |
   109	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/score-candidate.cjs` | Modify | Add `mode` field to all records (incl. infra_failure) |
   110	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/run-benchmark.cjs` | Modify | Add `mode` field to all records |
   111	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/promote-candidate.cjs` | Modify | Mode-aware status/convergence (extends existing scored/benchmark-complete branches) |
   112	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/reduce-state.cjs` | Modify | `mode` metadata pass-through + dashboard display (no structural change) |
   113	| `.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/scripts/tests/**` | Create | TST-1 identity gate + regression tests |
   114	<!-- /ANCHOR:scope -->
   115	
   116	---
   117	
   118	<!-- ANCHOR:requirements -->
   119	## 4. REQUIREMENTS
   120	
   121	### P0 - Blockers (MUST complete)
   122	
   123	| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
   124	|----|-------------|---------------------|
   125	| REQ-001 | Backward-compat: agent-improvement path unchanged | TST-1: `loop-host.cjs --mode=agent-improvement` vs no flag → byte-identical state JSONL (`diff` empty); deep-agent-improvement vitest suite stays green |
   126	| REQ-002 | Mode switch works end-to-end | `loop-host.cjs --mode=model-benchmark` materializes fixtures → runs benchmark → writes a `benchmark_run` record → `promote-candidate.cjs --mode=model-benchmark` returns a decision |
   127	| REQ-003 | Generic dispatcher | `dispatch-model.cjs` dispatches via executor-routing map; forwards `--variant` only for model-benchmark; never loaded in agent-improvement mode |
   128	
   129	### P1 - Required (complete OR user-approved deferral)
   130	
   131	| ID | Requirement | Acceptance Criteria |
   132	|----|-------------|---------------------|
   133	| REQ-004 | Scorer decoupled from fixture JSON | Scorer reads primitive criteria arrays (not raw fixture files); det-checks are cwd-decoupled — the scorer synthesizes a virtual fixture with an ABSOLUTE `scope.cwd`, and det-checks resolve `path.resolve(PACKET_ROOT, scope.cwd)` (a no-op for an absolute path), so no packet-relative coupling remains (122 review F-P2-3: this supersedes the earlier "det-checks accept explicit `--cwd`" wording — the decoupling is achieved via the absolute virtual-fixture cwd, not a literal flag); `buildGraderFn(mode)` factory in place |
   134	| REQ-005 | Edge cases handled | EC-1..10 from research §9 covered (unknown-mode default+warn, mode in infra_failure records, per-mode cache key, concurrent state-log safety, materialize-failure propagation) |
   135	<!-- /ANCHOR:requirements -->
   136	
   137	---
   138	
   139	<!-- ANCHOR:success-criteria -->
   140	## 5. SUCCESS CRITERIA
   141	
   142	- **SC-001**: TST-1 identity gate passes and is wired as a pre-merge check — the agent-improvement path is provably unaffected.
   143	- **SC-002**: A real `--mode=model-benchmark` run produces a scored `benchmark_run` record and a promotion decision, with every record carrying the correct `mode`.
   144	<!-- /ANCHOR:success-criteria -->
   145	
   146	---
   147	
   148	<!-- ANCHOR:risks -->
   149	## 6. RISKS & DEPENDENCIES
   150	
   151	| Type | Item | Impact | Mitigation |
   152	|------|------|--------|------------|
   153	| Risk | Modifying live deep-agent-improvement scripts regresses agent-improvement | High | TST-1 byte-identity gate + run the existing vitest suite before/after every change |
   154	| Risk | Scorer fixture-coupling decoupling is the hardest part (3 coupling points + det-check scripts) | Med | Land the additive new files first; decouple incrementally with the scorer's own tests |
   155	| Dependency | 120/003 port source (`eval-rig/`, `dispatch-minimax.cjs`, grader) | Med | Verified present; copy/port rather than reference cross-packet at runtime |
   156	| Risk | promote-candidate already branches on benchmark-complete (partial mode-awareness) | Low | Extend the existing branch rather than bolt on `--mode` from scratch |
   157	<!-- /ANCHOR:risks -->
   158	
