.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md:16:Defines the input and output contract for the prompt-surface scorer and the output benchmark runner so deep-agent-improvement runs remain deterministic enough for bounded local experimentation.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md:35:Every agent file in `.opencode/agents/*.md` is evaluated using dynamic mode. The scorer generates a profile on the fly from the agent's own structure, rules, and permissions using `generate-profile.cjs`. No static profiles are shipped; dynamic mode is the sole scoring path.
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md:41:### Dynamic Mode (5-dimension, only mode)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md:43:The scorer runs dynamic 5-dimension evaluation by default:
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md:47:- `--weights=JSON` optional (override default dimension weights)
.opencode/skills/deep-agent-improvement/references/model-benchmark/evaluator_contract.md:52:- `--outputs-dir=PATH`
